♂ (NHMW), Iran: Hormozgan Province: 26 km S of Minab, 7.1974 (G. Pretzmann).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">The specific epithet is a noun in apposition, referring to an ancient Iranian people who spoke the Median language and inhabited an area known as Media between western and northern Iran.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
The new species differs from all congeners (as well as all other members of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Philodromidae" genus="Philodromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Philodromus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Philodromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu lato) by having 2 parallel, unspaced tibial apophyses of the same length (vs apophyses either absent, or 1 or 2 spaced and not of equal length) and sperm duct thick at proximal-prolateral part, as thick as retrolaterally (vs prolateral part gradually tapering and thinner than retrolateral part).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as in Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male dorsal habitus of Rhysodromus genoensis sp. nov. (A) and Rhysodromus medes sp. nov. (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.70408.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/573566" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">18B</figureCitation>
. Total length 4.07. Carapace 1.87 long, 1.60 wide. Eye sizes: AME: 0.11, ALE: 0.07, PME: 0.10, PLE: 0.11. Carapace, labium, chelicera, maxilla and sternum yellowish-brown. Legs pale, without annulations. Abdomen pale, with scattered thick dark setae. Spinnerets pale, unicolourous. Measurements of legs: I: 8.97 (2.52, 0.96, 2.41, 2.06, 1.02), II: 11.58 (3.20, 1.19, 3.10, 2.78, 1.31), III: 4.97 (1.52, 0.52, 1.07, 1.18, 0.68), IV: 8.54 (2.65, 0.75, 1.95, 2.23, 0.96).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Palp as in Figures 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Male palps of Rhysodromus genoensis sp. nov. (A, B) and Rhysodromus medes sp. nov. (C, D) A, C ventral B, D retrolateral. Abbreviation: Ta - tegular apophysis. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.70408.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/573567" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">19C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. SEM images of the male palp of Rhysodromus medes sp. nov. A ventral B retroventral. Abbreviation: Ta - tegular apophysis. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1054.70408.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/573569" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">21A, B</figureCitation>
; tibia ca 1.3 times longer than wide, with two apophyses, not spaced and equal in length, about 
<normalizedToken originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="tibia’s">tibia's</normalizedToken>
length, ventral one membranous and transparent, retrolateral one well sclerotized; cymbium 1.7 times longer than wide, with tip equal in length to tibial apophyses; tegulum oval, ca 1.8 times longer than wide; sperm duct thick, only 2.5 times thinner than 
<normalizedToken originalValue="tibia’s">tibia's</normalizedToken>
diameter, proximal-prolateral part as thick as retrolateral part, sharply tapering in distal half of tegulum; tegular apophysis (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Ta</emphasis>
) small, claw-like, located antero-retrolaterally; embolus large, about 0.63 of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="tegulum’s">tegulum's</normalizedToken>
length, base as wide as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
of tegulum, gradually tapering.
</paragraph>
